The Global Citizen Festival, launched in 2012, is an extension of the Global Poverty Project, an international pressure group that hopes to eliminate poverty by increasing the number of those actively fighting against it.
To secure a free ticket to the event (unless they were willing to buy a VIP ticket), interested people had to complete a number of missions or "actions", such as volunteering, sending an email to a global leader, calling or finding other meaningful ways to contribute to raising awareness about their goal of eliminating poverty.
But how successful is Global Citizen, while there are still 12 years left to achieve its goal?
