"With the support of the UK government, donors, national governments and members of the Global Citizens community like you, we can make the social injustice of malnutrition a footnote in history," said Tracy Ulman, ambassador of The Power of Nutrition, to the public during the live concert in London in April 2018.
The group also stated that following over 5,000 actions calling on the United Kingdom to improve nutrition for mothers and children, the government announced funding for a project called The Power of Nutrition, addressed to 5 million women and children with dietary interventions.
Answering the question "What makes you think that we can eliminate extreme poverty?" included in the site's frequent questions,
a member of the Global Citizen community replied: "The road will be long and difficult, sometimes we will fall and fail.
But like all major human rights movements and against apartheid before us, we will succeed, because united we are stronger.
