The application uses Solid platform technology allowing users to create their own "personal electronic data storage space" or a POD.
It may contain lists of contacts, lists of pending work, calendar, music library and other personal and professional tools.
It's like Google Drive, Microsoft Outlook, Slack and Spotify are all available in a browser and all at the same time.
The unique feature of the data storage personal is that it allows the user to decide who has access to what kind of information.
The company calls this possibility "personal empowerment through data".
Inrupt's idea, according to company CEO John Bruce, is the company to offer resources, processes and appropriate skills so that the Solid platform is available to everyone.
The company consists of Berners Lee, Bruce, a security platform purchased by IBM, some contracted developers who worked in the project and a community of code developers volunteers.
