Both of these charges bear the death penalty, according to the document.
Weeks after the attack, a federal jury brought Shaipof up against the 22-point indictment, involving eight counts of homicide in favor of a criminal organization, a tactic often applied by federal prosecutors in organised crime cases and a charge of violence and destruction of motor vehicles.
