It has been ten years since the South District Court of New York prosecuted a case that carries the death penalty.
The defendant, Khalid Barnes, was convicted of the murder of two drug dealers, but was eventually sentenced to life imprisonment in September 2009.
The last time a death sentence was imposed on a federal case in New York was in 1953 on the husbands Julius and Ethel Rosenberg, executed after being convicted of conspiracy to commit espionage in favour of the Soviet Union during the Cold War two years ago.
